# Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA) Project

## Objective
Analyze the Titanic dataset to uncover patterns, trends, and relationships using statistical summaries and visualizations.

## Technologies Used
- Python
- Pandas
- Matplotlib
- Seaborn
- Google Colab

## Tasks Performed
- Data exploration
- Statistical analysis
- Handling missing values
- Data visualization
- Correlation analysis

## Visualizations
- Survival Count
- Passenger Class Distribution
- Gender Distribution
- Age Distribution
- Fare Distribution
- Correlation Heatmap

## Key Insights
- Passenger class influenced survival rates.
- Female passengers had higher survival chances.
- Most passengers were between 20–40 years old.
- Fare prices varied significantly among passengers.

## Outcome
Learned analytical thinking, data exploration, and visualization techniques.
